svg.title: The layout of the Odell apartment’s living-room. The fireplace is built into the west wall, and is flanked by a Boule cabinet and an escritoire. Before the fireplace is a davenport, and a cross mark on the davenport is labeled “where Margaret Odell was strangled.” Behind the davenport is a narrow table with a lamp. Along the east wall is a gate-leg table with a mirror, and the passage to the bedroom. The north wall is taken up by three large windows. A door on the south wall opens into a large clothes closet, and another pair of doors leads out into a small foyer, which in turn leads to the apartment’s entrance.
